lic service and training.  Those units that offer degree programs or provide credit courses in support of other degree programs are shown on the primary organization chart.  Centers/institutes indicated with a "+" have been exempted by the Provost and Vice President for Academic Affairs from periodic review under UNT Policy 06.046 because the primary mission of each unit is to provide educational support and/or provide internship sites for its constituent academic unit. Office of the Provost and Vice President for Academic Affairs Office of Research and Economic Development Center for Advanced Research and Technology Center for Advanced Scientific Computing and Modeling Center for Computational Epidemiology and Response Analysis College of Arts and Sciences Castleberry Peace Institute Center for Economic Education Center for Environmental Economic Studies and Research Center for Environmental Philosophy+ Center for Network Neuroscience Center for Nonlinear Science Center for Plant Lipid Research Center for Psychosocial Health Research Center for Sport Psychology and Performance Excellence Center for Watershed Reservoir Assessment and Management Institute of Applied Sciences Center for Remote Sensing Elm Fork Education Center Military History Center Center for Economic Development and Research  UNT Speech and Hearing Center+ College of Business Institute of Petroleum Accounting College of Education Bill J. Priest Center for Community College Education Center for Play Therapy Center for Sport Psychology and Performance Excellence Counseling and Human Development Center+ College of Engineering Center for Information and Cyber Security Net-Centric Software and Systems Center PACCAR Technology Institute College of Information Center for Knowledge Solutions Institute for the Integration of Technology into Teaching and Learning Texas Center for Educational Technology College of Merchandising, Hospitality and Tourism global Digital Retailing Research Center College of Music